<br />

<br />
Belanar is approaching this discussion purely from the perspective of a post-elemental, level 65, mega-AA enchanter, and his buddies of similar capability.
<br />

<br />
Believe it or not, for people for whom Execution is a challenge, mez is not a crutch, it is vital, because all of our warriors don't have AE Taunt with enough hp that CHeal is partial and all of our clerics don't have 6000 mana pools.  We can't do trials with 4 people, and let a couple ride along.  <span style="font-style: italic">All</span> of the group DPS is needed for each mob in a wave, to get it dead in 30 seconds.  Yes, we can occasionally off-tank a non-mezzable mob, but we eat up mana and health in the process, which we can hopefully recover in-between waves.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=304783" target="_blank" class="postlink">Fallere T`Vala</a>
