                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Charming isn't about controlling the 1 mob, it's about the damage the charmed pet does to the mob you are trying to kill.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, since I play a cleric and not a druid it was much easier for me to avoid aggro. It might be that if you only have druids to heal that you have to use mez, I don't know.
<br />

<br />
What I know is that after I looked at the different strategies people were using I came up with one that got our groups through nearly every time (when someone didn't screw up) regardless of which mobs spawned.
<br />

<br />
Oh, yeah, I remember now another reason I didn't like to mez things is that I'd usually have a druid or mage DS on everyone and by the time we got to the 4th mob it was already half dead from that. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
I also ran groups through hanging whenever the line for exe was too long but it was harder convincing people to do that then to use my tactics for exe...
<br />

<br />
I should have tried harder to get people into other trials. In retrospect I think stoning or torture might be easier than exe or hanging... it's hard to tell going in with today's equipment though.
<br />

