                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I must say I played around in the trials just once one night for about a half dozen attempts.  At first I went with the exp tank telling me to use my AoE stuns, which were basically fully resisted and I was just getting beat on hard.  I switched away from that method and went to mezzing the Fiend like creatures and using my animation to off tank a second rock guy, rooting third or forth rock men.  
<br />

<br />
I found that I could stand up on the stage in Exe, and cast AoE mezz into the wave as the tank gathered them into the center.  This worked pretty well with an occasional resist who I would just use Gok to mezz after they came after me.  My pet did very well against the rockmen off tanking them until the Tank and DPS crowd were rdy to move onto them.
<br />

<br />
While we didnt win during these 6 tries we did very well for 5 people who had never been there, on being a 53 monk, and 1 exp'd tank leading us.
<br />

<br />
Oh and using the mezz feature rather then chaining in stuns allowed me to Nuke as needed on the MoBs and Save mana for the big guy in the end.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=715917" target="_blank" class="postlink"> Majority Rulz </a>
