                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Execution trial is pretty easy, as most all of the mobs are stunnable, even tho the rocks give a message that they're immune to the stun effect (they still stop attacking, so I don't care that they think they're immune).
<br />

<br />
If I chain-stun, that means that effectively, I tank all 4 waves.   I rune first, then AE tash (As, they are pretty resistant, but not after tash), and then chain 3 color stuns while my group focuses and kills them.  Clerics and druids in my group heal me inbetween waves, but when mobs are up, they are dps.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378985" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tashim</a>, 65th Enchanter
<br />
<a href="http://www.drow.org/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Blood of the Spider</a>, <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Rathe</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
